&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; The path that *actually* worshiped Her, was/is =\r\nTantra, which believes, there is no &quot;Avidya&quot; at all. Brahman/the-state-call=\r\ned-Atman is true, and so is the world of duality which is but a manifestati=\r\non/projection of that core. In the path of Tantra, which was neither mainst=\r\nream nor geographically widespread, there was never any restriction to fema=\r\nles with respect to sadhana. Not only were women initiated, but there were =\r\nfantastic women of exceptional spiritual caliber, and they used to be class=\r\nified based on the levels they had achieved as &quot;uttara-sadhikas&quot;, &quot;bhairavi=\r\ns&quot; and &quot;yoginis&quot;. While mainstream Hinduism was busy burning widows alive i=\r\nn the name of some dubious rules, Tantras boldly declared Sati-daha as an a=\r\nbomination, rejected the caste-system totally, and allowed women the status=\r\n of spiritual preceptors when they could attain certain states. One of the =\r\nGurus of Sri Ramakrishna was a Bhairavi who taught him Tantra. The first pe=\r\nrson to\n worship&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  UgraTara south of the Vindya Hills was the wife =\r\nof a disciple of Sri Ramana Maharishi, who was initiated into this worship =\r\nby a Bhairavi in Mithila. If a Bhairavi has the caliber to teach a Ramakris=\r\nhna, would she not have the caliber to act as gurus for average folks? Sure=\r\n. But then, history does not even record her real name. Why? Because, the s=\r\nystem of Tantra as well as those who followed the path - both men and women=\r\n - were firmly rejected by mainstream brahminical Hinduism; thus they never=\r\n gained any popularity, except for the wrong reasons. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; Every worship of Durga that happens anywhere today is India is sti=\r\nll a watered-down version from the Tantras. The concept of ChanDi Homa was =\r\nfirst mentioned in the Damara and Katyayani Tantras. In Bengal every rule o=\r\nf Durga Puja is from the various Tantric schools. [For example, when creati=\r\nng an idol of Durga, the mud has to be collected from 4/5 different places =\r\nsuch as from home of a prostitute, a river-bed, a widow&#39;s house, etc etc.] =\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; So it is not that those who followed the path=\r\n of Ma Durga never had women saints. Infact, they had more women in their f=\r\nolds who were accorded the highest spiritual status than in mainstream Hind=\r\nuism. But since Tantra itself was never popular, neither were these saints =\r\npopular. And things like female foeticide were unheard of in places where t=\r\nhe worship of the Goddess was popular. Even the misguided thugees - infamou=\r\ns worshipers of Ma Kali - who were guilty of rampant human-sacrifices, woul=\r\nd never dare to offer a woman as a sacrifice to Ma Kali, for they feared of=\r\n Her wrath since Tantras strictly forbid harming the female of any specifie=\r\ns for a worshiper of the Goddess. So if blame has to be laid for mistreatme=\r\nnt of women, objectively it would not fall on those whose chief worship was=\r\n of Durga or Kali or one of Her forms.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; -Regard=\r\ns&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Bazeecha-e-atf=\r\nal hain duniya mere aage.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Hota hain shab-o-roz tamasha mere aage&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Ek khel hain aurang-e-sulemaan mere nazdeek&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; Ek baat hain ijaz-e-masiah mere aage.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\n________________________________&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  From: sunrise_1080 &lt;sunrise_1=\r\n080@...&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; To: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom=\r\n%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;/mc/compose?to=3Dvedic-wisdom=\r\n%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt; &lt